#. <section class="sutta" id="mn46"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn46:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 46"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn46:0.2"
msgid "Mahādhammasamādānasutta"
msgstr "The Great Discourse on Taking Up Practices"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.310"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn46:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn46:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn46:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn46:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn46:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn46:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn46:2.1"
msgid "“yebhuyyena, bhikkhave, sattā evaṅkāmā evaṃchandā evaṃadhippāyā:"
msgstr "“Mendicants, sentient beings typically have the wish, desire, and hope:"

msgctxt "mn46:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘aho vata aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā parihāyeyyuṃ, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā "
"dhammā abhivaḍḍheyyun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh, if only unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable things would decrease, "
"and likable, desirable, and agreeable things would increase!’"

msgctxt "mn46:2.3"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ, bhikkhave, sattānaṃ evaṅkāmānaṃ evaṃchandānaṃ evaṃadhippāyānaṃ "
"aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā "
"parihāyanti."
msgstr "But exactly the opposite happens to them."

msgctxt "mn46:2.4"
msgid "Tatra tumhe, bhikkhave, kaṃ hetuṃ paccethā”ti?"
msgstr "What do you take to be the reason for this?”"

msgctxt "mn46:2.5"
msgid ""
"“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā, bhagavaṃnettikā, bhagavaṃpaṭisaraṇā. "
"Sādhu vata, bhante, bhagavantaññeva paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho; "
"bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. He is our guide and our refuge. "
"Sir, may the Buddha himself please clarify the meaning of this. The "
"mendicants will listen and remember it.”"

msgctxt "mn46:2.6"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn46:2.7"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn46:2.8"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn46:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano, ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa "
"akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa "
"akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto, "
msgstr ""
"“Take an uneducated ordinary person who has not seen the noble ones, and is "
"neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not "
"seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of "
"the good persons. "

msgctxt "mn46:3.2"
msgid ""
"sevitabbe dhamme na jānāti asevitabbe dhamme na jānāti, bhajitabbe dhamme na "
"jānāti abhajitabbe dhamme na jānāti."
msgstr ""
"They don’t know what practices they should cultivate and foster, and what "
"practices they shouldn’t cultivate and foster."

msgctxt "mn46:3.3"
msgid ""
"So sevitabbe dhamme ajānanto asevitabbe dhamme ajānanto, bhajitabbe dhamme "
"ajānanto abhajitabbe dhamme ajānanto, asevitabbe dhamme sevati sevitabbe "
"dhamme na sevati, abhajitabbe dhamme bhajati bhajitabbe dhamme na bhajati."
msgstr ""
"So they cultivate and foster practices they shouldn’t, and don’t cultivate "
"and foster practices they should."

msgctxt "mn46:3.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa asevitabbe dhamme sevato sevitabbe dhamme asevato, abhajitabbe dhamme "
"bhajato bhajitabbe dhamme abhajato aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā "
"abhivaḍḍhanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā parihāyanti."
msgstr ""
"When they do so, unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable things increase, "
"and likable, desirable, and agreeable things decrease."

msgctxt "mn46:3.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn46:3.6"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ aviddasuno."
msgstr "Because that’s what it’s like for someone who doesn’t know."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn46:4.1"
msgid ""
"Sutavā ca kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako, ariyānaṃ dassāvī ariyadhammassa "
"kovido ariyadhamme suvinīto, sappurisānaṃ dassāvī sappurisadhammassa kovido "
"sappurisadhamme suvinīto, "
msgstr ""
"But an educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is skilled and "
"trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve seen good persons, and "
"are skilled and trained in the teaching of the good persons. "

msgctxt "mn46:4.2"
msgid ""
"sevitabbe dhamme jānāti asevitabbe dhamme jānāti, bhajitabbe dhamme jānāti "
"abhajitabbe dhamme jānāti."
msgstr ""
"They know what practices they should cultivate and foster, and what "
"practices they shouldn’t cultivate and foster."

msgctxt "mn46:4.3"
msgid ""
"So sevitabbe dhamme jānanto asevitabbe dhamme jānanto, bhajitabbe dhamme "
"jānanto abhajitabbe dhamme jānanto, asevitabbe dhamme na sevati sevitabbe "
"dhamme sevati, abhajitabbe dhamme na bhajati bhajitabbe dhamme bhajati."
msgstr ""
"So they cultivate and foster practices they should, and don’t cultivate and "
"foster practices they shouldn’t."

msgctxt "mn46:4.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa asevitabbe dhamme asevato sevitabbe dhamme sevato, abhajitabbe dhamme "
"abhajato bhajitabbe dhamme bhajato, aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā "
"parihāyanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti."
msgstr ""
"When they do so, unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable things decrease, "
"and likable, desirable, and agreeable things increase."

msgctxt "mn46:4.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn46:4.6"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ viddasuno."
msgstr "Because that’s what it’s like for someone who knows."

